apping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNMultiPolyline","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","fragments":[{"text":"MLNMultiPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapView/addAnnotation:":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"addAnnotation:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/addannotation:","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addAnnotation:"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds an annotation to the map view."}],"title":"addAnnotation:","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNPointCollection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disconnected vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPointCollection"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"text":" instances, and the line segments that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"path along which something moves.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolyline"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNPolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapView":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNMapView","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview","abstract":[{"text":"An interactive, customizable map view with an interface similar to the one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"provided by Apple’s MapKit.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","title":"MLNMapView"}}}